What is friendship? What’s that thing that you look for in someone OR hope to be for someone? So many answers came through the “feelings check” question I asked the other day in my stories about friendship… and at the core of many of them were just about the need of someone to “just be there”. Someone to walk life with. This song came out of a write the other day with @samtinnesz and @ottoblueofficial and I felt like it was powerful. We need people. Children need their parents, spouses need one another… friends need friends… and we all want the real thing. Someone to be there. ❤️ love y’all. Thank you for always answering my questions with raw honesty and pure depth. I don’t share original often BUT I hope this guides you in some way. #illbethereforyou #friendsgiving #loveyou #motherhood

I was FaceTiming my Mom earlier… which to her is a great gift for Mother’s Day. Living a state away and not seeing my parents as often as I’d like always hits me on holidays. I think some of it has to do with time, growing older but not apart… only closer even with distance. There is a depth that really develops and also a longing. In my 20’s I really dove into trying to get to know my parents better… outside of a childhood mindset and as an adult. I never gave my mom enough credit as a kid… as a problem child but she gave me all the love that she could ever imagine… while I drug myself through the mud. As I get older, it just adds up more and more. She is someone I will walk with and walk for… no matter what. I put her through hell… and she loves me still. Until I no longer can, I will, without any hesitation, return that love and multiply it. I love you mom. #mothersday #mommyandme #hereforyou #illalwaysloveyou #growingup

Growing up, I was an outsider. I didn’t dress like everyone else around me, I had different interests, my family life looked very different than any one I knew… a lot of that added up to me feeling really lonely and just lost. I felt like a burden and honestly unlovable. I did not have to the tools to be able to love myself because I didn’t feel like anyone else could. I’d put a mask on and try and not stick out… but at some point around high school I leaned into my heart and soul. I had to stop caring  because I was so uncomfortably unhappy. I remember walking into my first highschool class and a few upper class came up to me and said “yesss an emo kid”… haha I was standing there with my checkered vans, checkered backpack and famous stars and straps belt buckle… my people found me. I’m still friends with them to this day. Those relationships lead me into finding who I am. Yes I have seasons of unhealthy, YES as a guy I feel uncomfortable or insecure with how I look more often than not… but it’s MY PEOPLE who shed the light and remind me it’s about my heart and my soul and how I’m able to love people as a result of loving myself. I know… big caption BUT I really love being able to peak into what @cimorelliband is doing. Their hearts are so solid and they are so kind and generous BUT these words have such a depth to them and are such a great reminder for EVERYONE. Thankful I get to spend some time with them. #loveyourself #loveyourskin #youareenough #youareworthy #youarenotalone #cimorelli
